      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BETTY BULLPIT (7) comes off a moderate effort last start, finishing fifth at this track over 520m behind Spring Drop (30.09). Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Key runner on her best form. TEQUILA GIRL (6) steps out a further 119m to an untried trip. Comes here after a last start 7th and beaten 17 lengths (24.41) at this track. Can feature in the finish. GRAND FORTE (1) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Maiden at Maitland over 450m. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Rates a winning chance on best. BLUE MOET (8) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
